The paper deals with the design of circuits that can correctly sort inputs that may contain metastable bits. This is a problem that arises in digital electronics, which falls under the category of Electronic Design Automation (EDA). Specifically, the paper deals with the design of sorting networks, which are used to sort inputs in a variety of applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.ET (Electronic Design Automation), followed by cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
